%% Journey 3: User Task Lifecycle
%% A user task is created, assigned, and completed through Tasklist.

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Engine as Engine
    participant Log as Log Stream
    participant CExp as Camunda Exporter
    participant ES as Elasticsearch
    participant Search as Search Client
    participant TL as Tasklist
    participant User as End User
    participant GW as REST Gateway
    participant Broker as Broker

    Engine->>Log: USER_TASK:CREATING (engine hits user task element)
    Engine->>Log: USER_TASK:CREATED
    Log->>CExp: Export USER_TASK records
    CExp->>ES: Index user task (state: CREATED)

    User->>TL: Open Tasklist UI
    TL->>Search: Search user tasks (filtered by assignee / candidate)
    Search->>ES: HTTP query
    ES-->>Search: Results
    Search-->>TL: UserTaskEntity[]
    TL-->>User: Display tasks

    User->>TL: Claim task
    TL->>GW: POST /v2/user-tasks/{id}/assignment
    GW->>Broker: BrokerAssignUserTaskRequest
    Broker->>Engine: USER_TASK:ASSIGN
    Engine->>Log: USER_TASK:ASSIGNED
    Log->>CExp: Export assignment
    CExp->>ES: Update task assignee

    User->>User: Fill in form / provide data

    User->>TL: Complete task
    TL->>GW: POST /v2/user-tasks/{id}/completion
    GW->>Broker: BrokerCompleteUserTaskRequest
    Broker->>Engine: USER_TASK:COMPLETE
    Engine->>Log: USER_TASK:COMPLETED
    Engine->>Log: VARIABLE:CREATED (form output)

    Note over Engine,Log: Engine advances process past user task

    Log->>CExp: Export completion
    CExp->>ES: Update task state to COMPLETED
